# vantage-web rules

Static site (Zola + Tailwind v4) for vantage-ui.com. Built with `make build`
(`tailwindcss -i css/main.css -o static/main.css` then `zola build`); deployed
to S3 + CloudFront by `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`. `static/main.css` is a
gitignored build output — only the `css/main.css` source is committed.

## Changelog (synced — do not hand-edit)

The release notes on `/download` are synced **automatically** from `vantage-ui`
(its `release.yaml` writes `static/changelog-*.md` and the `changelog_minors` /
`[extra.changelog_dates]` blocks in `content/download.md` on every release).
Do not hand-edit those — a future `chore: sync changelog` commit overwrites them.

## Release-note screenshots (website-owned)

Screenshots are a separate layer the sync never touches:

- **Mapping:** `static/changelog-screenshots.yaml`, keyed by minor version.
- **Images:** `static/images/changelog/<minor>/NN.webp` (thumb) + `NN-full.webp`.
- **Render:** `themes/vantage/templates/download.html` draws a `.shot-grid` of
  thumbnails under each version; clicking opens the lightbox (overlay in
  `base.html`, behaviour in `static/js/site.js`, styles in `css/main.css`).

### Adding screenshots for a release

1. Take macOS **window captures** (⌘⇧4 then Space) — they come on a transparent
   canvas with a drop shadow; the script crops to the window automatically.
2. Run the ingest, passing alternating `path` then `caption` arguments:
   ```
   script/add-screenshots 0.18 \
     ~/Desktop/screenshots/a.png "Caption A" \
     ~/Desktop/screenshots/b.png "Caption B"
   ```
   It crops each window out of the shadow (via its alpha bounding box), writes a
   fast-load thumb + a fullscreen WebP, and updates the YAML idempotently
   (re-running for the same minor replaces that block; other minors are kept).
   Captions are optional — omit to fall back to generic alt text.
3. Commit the new YAML + `static/images/changelog/<minor>/`.

Screenshots for an **unreleased** version (e.g. 0.18 before it ships) sit
dormant: they only render once that minor appears in `changelog_minors`, which
happens when the release publishes and syncs. To preview earlier, temporarily
add the minor to `changelog_minors` + a stub `changelog-<minor>.md`,
`zola build`, then revert.
